   note = {ISI Document Delivery No.: EI7TS Times Cited: 2 Cited Reference Count: 93 Hillmann, Felicitas Ziegelmayer, Usha Volkswagen Stiftung This article is based on the research results within the project "New Regional Formations: rapid environmental change and migration in coastal areas in Ghana and Indonesia", funded by Volkswagen Stiftung. The project consortium was coordinated by the University of Bremen (lead) and the Leibniz Institute for Research on Society and Space in Erkner near Berlin. The overall project is divided into five subprojects that were run by the ZMT (Centre for Marine Tropical Ecology, Bremen), the Jacobs University (Bremen) and the KWI in Essen in the years 2014-2016. The results presented here were gathered within subproject 3, titled: Migrant trajectories. The authors want to express their gratitude for the generous funding by Volkswagen Stiftung. 2 0 3 Gesellschaft erdkunde berlin Berlin},
